cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE 

This paper is about word embedding models, which are commonly used in natural language processing (NLP) tasks such as clustering and relationship inference. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which focuses on NLP and related topics. The paper also proposes a solution that involves generating synthetic data points, which suggests a connection to machine learning and generative models, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of linear operations in embedded space, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the paper's focus on aligning variations of the same model suggests a connection to neural networks (cs.NE).
